@CaptainQuahog, cogent? OK, I guess the criticism was cogent, in that it was readily understandable. 

However, the criticism was in no way constructive that I noticed. Just (to paraphrase): this doesn't measure up to an arbitrary Sunday puzzle (which, not for nothing, gave that creator nearly twice the grid area [441 squares vs. this puzzle's 225] to develop its concept) from 13 years ago that the columnist considers superior to this one.

The column does not need to be relentlessly positive. But if the columnist doesn't include actual, helpful, constructive criticism, then the negative aspects of the column come off as a bit jaded and sniping.
